

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="mysticism"
  description="mysticism index / synchronicity, vision, revelation, the unknown, and hidden meaning"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">mysticism / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>mysticism</h1>
    <p>
      synchronicity, vision, revelation, hidden meaning, and experiences that
      seem to exceed ordinary explanation. mysticism begins where reality feels
      charged with more than surface causality.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      this wing explores threshold experiences, meaningful coincidence, symbolic
      vision, and the strange sense that life sometimes speaks through events.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/mysticism/synchronicity">
          <span class="link-title">synchronicity</span>
          <span class="link-desc">meaningful coincidence, acausal connection, and symbolic pattern.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/mysticism/vision">
          <span class="link-title">vision</span>
          <span class="link-desc">inner sight, imaginal encounters, and revelatory images.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/mysticism/revelation">
          <span class="link-title">revelation</span>
          <span class="link-desc">sudden knowing, disclosure, and the shock of insight.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/mysticism/the-unknown">
          <span class="link-title">the unknown</span>
          <span class="link-desc">mystery, uncertainty, and what remains beyond explanation.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/mysticism/hidden-meaning">
          <span class="link-title">hidden meaning</span>
          <span class="link-desc">symbolic depth, concealed pattern, and layered significance.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to read</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        mysticism should not be reduced too quickly to either literal certainty
        or total dismissal. it belongs to the charged middle ground where image,
        feeling, symbol, and event begin to gather unusual significance.
      </p>
      <p>
        read this section with patience. the point is not to force belief, but
        to stay close to the texture of experiences that feel larger than their
        ordinary explanation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">mysticism map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/mysticism/synchronicity" class="link-blue">synchronicity</a> — coincidence, pattern, acausal meaning</p>
      <p><a href="/mysticism/vision" class="link-red">vision</a> — imaginal sight, image, revelation</p>
      <p><a href="/mysticism/revelation" class="link-green">revelation</a> — disclosure, insight, sudden knowing</p>
      <p><a href="/mysticism/the-unknown">the unknown</a> — mystery, uncertainty, limit</p>
      <p><a href="/mysticism/hidden-meaning">hidden meaning</a> — depth, symbol, concealed pattern</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">note</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this wing is arranged as a circular path: synchronicity → vision → revelation
        → the unknown → hidden meaning → back to synchronicity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>